            "format": "basic_html",
            "processed": "Depending on the segmentation method you used (StarDist3D or U-Net3D), you may also cite either of following papers:  <br>Martin Weigert, Uwe Schmidt, Robert Haase, Ko Sugawara, and Gene Myers. Star-convex Polyhedra for 3D Object Detection and Segmentation in Microscopy. The IEEE Winter Conference on Applications of Computer Vision (WACV), Snowmass Village, Colorado, March 2020  <br>\u00c7i\u00e7ek, \u00d6., Abdulkadir, A., Lienkamp, S.S., Brox, T., Ronneberger, O. (2016). 3D U-Net: Learning Dense Volumetric Segmentation from Sparse Annotation. In: Ourselin, S., Joskowicz, L., Sabuncu, M., Unal, G., Wells, W. (eds) Medical Image Computing and Computer-Assisted Intervention \u2013 MICCAI 2016. MICCAI 2016. Lecture Notes in Computer Science, vol 9901. Springer, Cham.",
